    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** and **Kyle Tucker** anchoring the lineup as the clear elite starts. **Gunnar Henderson** earns a dominant 81.87 score, buoyed by an ideal 16% park factor and a favorable matchup against R. Nelson, while **Kyle Tucker** (72.86) remains a must-start despite the left-on-left dynamic against D. Peterson, as his elite profile and wind-assisted power potential override the platoon split. **Luis Robert Jr.** and **Josh Lowe** also provide significant upside; specifically, the 85% SB-success probability against Wrobleski\u2019s slow delivery makes **Luis Robert Jr.** a critical asset for our strategy, as he is the primary engine for keeping our team competitive in the league's scarcest category.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision was bypassing **Nasim Nunez**, who finished with a 38.00 score. While his profile is usually relevant for our SB-heavy build, the aggressive matchup against Skenes cratered his efficiency score, forcing us to prioritize the higher floor of **Josh Jung** and **Andy Pages**. We are closely monitoring the risk profile of **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, who draws the daunting assignment of Skenes today; his 19% SP skill penalty suggests a low-scoring ceiling, but his role at the top of the order keeps him in the lineup. Conversely, we are keeping a close eye on the health status of **Jordan Westburg**, whose absence continues to tighten our depth, and we remain cautious regarding the weather flags impacting our park-adjusted projections across the board.",
